Popular media personality, Toke Makinwa has revealed the extent she had to go at one point to satiate her craving for Chinese cuisine. The OAP, in an insta story post, informed her fans that she once booked ticket and flew on on a commercial plane just to go enjoy some Hakkasan goodness. “But to be honest I’ve woken up with a craving for hakkasan and I booked a ticket to have it for dinner sha.   15 reasons you should drink enough water daily     Protests as truck kills two in Lagos     Bandits kill DPO, six others in Niger   “Not a private plane but I took myself to London to eat hakkasan too…. Ok bye.” Hakkasan is modern Chinese cuisine restaurant brand London that offers guests a world-class culinary experience. Its menu includes signature dishes such as the Crispy duck salad and Hakka steamed dim sum platter or the Jasmine tea smoked short rib.